## Key Skills

- **Clutch Putting**: 100/100 - The most clutch putter in major championship history — his ability to make crucial putts under maximum pressure was unmatched.
- **Mental Toughness**: 100/100 - Transformed golf's psychological dimension. Opponents described feeling 'Tigered' — overwhelmed by his presence before the tournament began.
- **Power**: 98/100 - His physical transformation in the late 1990s produced drives that were 20-30 yards longer than competitors, changing how golf was played.
- **Course Management**: 95/100 - Knew when to be aggressive and when to play percentage golf. His strategic intelligence was a weapon even when his physical game was not firing.
